Quick guide for enabling ACRA in an application


0) Initialize this library 

        android update project -p `pwd` -t android-15


1) reference this library in project properties 

          android.library.reference.1=../acra


2) add or descend from

     <application
        android:name="com.partech.acra.BasicApplication"

3) add the imports to the Activity:


 import com.partech.acra.*;
 import java.io.*;
 import android.os.Environment;

4) add this code to the onCreate (don't forget to tweak the log filename):

        final File path = new File(Environment.getExternalStorageDirectory() + "/acra/");
        try {
            path.mkdirs();

            File logs = new File(path, "logs");
            logs.mkdir();
            CrashHandler.instance().initialize(logs.toString() + "/" + "gvtether_crash_");

            Log.d(TAG, "initialized logging directory: " + logs);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            Log.d(TAG, "could not create: " + path);
        }





